Bay St. Louis, MS is a city along the Mississippi Gulf Coast with a humid subtropical climate characterized by hot, humid summers and mild to cool, humid winters. It is located on the western shore of the Bay of St. Louis with the Gulf of Mexico to the south. The current NOAA weather station has been installed on a piling just offshore of the Waveland CLub since November 2005 following Hurricane Katrina.
